<section class="page-header page-shell">
  <div>
    <a href="/admin/dashboard" class="btn-link">&larr; Back to dashboard</a>
    <h1>Workflow help</h1>
    <p class="muted">Step-by-step guidance for running schedule-based events and food prep-style sign-ups.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="page-section page-shell">
  <article class="card card--plain">
    <h2>Scheduled events (stations & time slots)</h2>
    <ol class="muted">
      <li><strong>Create the event:</strong> Click “Create new event”, enter name/description, set Start and End, choose “Volunteer schedule”. Save.</li>
      <li><strong>Add stations:</strong> Click “Add station”, enter Station name and description/duties. Save.</li>
      <li><strong>Add time blocks:</strong> In each station card, press “Add time block”. Set Start, End, and Slots (capacity), then Save.</li>
      <li><strong>Add consecutive blocks quickly:</strong> After saving a block, use the “Add next block” button in that station to prefill the next Start/End based on the prior duration, adjust if needed, then Save.</li>
      <li><strong>Reorder stations:</strong> Click “Reorder stations”. Drag the ☰ handle to reorder, or press “Sort by date & time” to auto-order, then OK.</li>
      <li><strong>Publish:</strong> Press “Publish” so volunteers can see and sign up. Unpublish to hide it again.</li>
      <li><strong>Move volunteers:</strong> Click a filled slot’s “Move”, pick the new station/time, and confirm.</li>
      <li><strong>Adjust slots:</strong> Click the Slots number in a station card to edit capacity, then save.</li>
      <li><strong>Print/export:</strong> Use “Actions → Printable PDF” or “Actions → Quick Export/Advanced Export” for rosters.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="muted small">Tip: keep station descriptions brief; use <code>**bold**</code> for key instructions.</p>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="page-section page-shell">
  <article class="card card--plain">
    <h2>Food Prep events (categories & items, no times)</h2>
    <ol class="muted">
      <li><strong>Create the event:</strong> Click “Create new event” and choose “Food Prep (categories & items, no times)”. Save.</li>
      <li><strong>Add categories:</strong> Click “Add category”, name it (e.g., Main dishes, Sides), add a short description. Save.</li>
      <li><strong>Add items:</strong> Within a category, click “Add item”. Enter Item name and optional Feeds (min/max). Save.</li>
      <li><strong>Reorder items:</strong> Click “Manage → Reorder items…” in a category (or “Reorder items” in the modal) and drag ☰ to set the display order.</li>
      <li><strong>Reorder categories:</strong> Click “Reorder categories”, drag ☰ to set order, then OK.</li>
      <li><strong>Publish:</strong> Press “Publish”. Volunteers choose items directly; capacity is the number of items.</li>
      <li><strong>Collect notes:</strong> Volunteers can add dish notes; see them in the roster and exports.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="muted small">Tip: set Feeds ranges (e.g., 6–8) on items so you can balance sign-ups.</p>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="page-section page-shell">
  <article class="card card--plain">
    <h2>Common tasks</h2>
    <ul class="muted">
      <li><strong>Move a volunteer:</strong> On the event page, select a reservation’s “Move” option and pick a new slot.</li>
      <li><strong>Adjust capacity:</strong> Click a station’s slot count to edit capacity inline.</li>
      <li><strong>Reorder stations/items:</strong> Use “Reorder stations” (or “Reorder categories” in food prep mode) and drag the ☰ handles. For food prep events, open a category → “Manage → Reorder items…” and drag to reorder. You can also auto-sort stations by date &amp; time in the reorder modal.</li>
      <li><strong>Close sign-ups:</strong> Unpublish the event to hide it from volunteers without deleting data.</li>
      <li><strong>Duplicate an event:</strong> Use “Copy event” to clone structure (stations/slots) without volunteers.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="page-section page-shell">
  <article class="card card--plain">
    <h2 id="visibility">Publish & visibility</h2>
    <ul class="muted">
      <li><strong>Draft</strong>: Only admins can view (preview). Hidden from the Upcoming Sign-ups list.</li>
      <li><strong>Private link</strong>: Hidden from the Upcoming Sign-ups list but reachable by anyone with the direct link.</li>
      <li><strong>Public</strong>: Listed on Upcoming Sign-ups and accessible by link.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="page-section page-shell">
  <article class="card card--plain">
    <h2>Need more help?</h2>
    <p class="muted">Formatting guide: <a href="/admin/help/formatting">open in a new window</a></p>
    <p class="muted small">For issues, capture a screenshot and the event URL to speed up troubleshooting.</p>
  </article>
</section>

